HEADWORD: Torpescent
<hw>Tor*pes"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>torpescens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>torpescere</ets> to grow stiff,
numb, or torpid, incho. fr. <ets>torpere</ets>. See
<er>Torpid</er>.]</ety> <def>Becoming torpid or numb.</def>
